#Bring in data
coh <- read_csv("data/posterData.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   age = col_integer(),
##   female = col_integer(),
##   full_ed = col_integer(),
##   child = col_integer(),
##   marital = col_character(),
##   practice = col_character(),
##   coherance = col_integer(),
##   coherance_mean = col_double(),
##   quallife = col_integer(),
##   quallife_mean = col_double(),
##   impact = col_integer(),
##   impact_mean = col_double()
## )
#Subset data into single only
sing <- coh %>% 
  filter(marital=="Single") %>% 
  rownames_to_column(var="NewID")

#Examine the categorical variable:
table(sing$practice)
## 
##  MedicalWard      Nursing SurgicalWard 
##           24           49           28
#Factor variables:
sing <- sing %>% 
  mutate(practice_f = factor(practice, levels=c("Nursing", "MedicalWard", "SurgicalWard")))

#Run the model (Nurs as reference)
qual <- lm(quallife_mean ~ age + practice_f + coherance_mean + practice_f*coherance_mean , data=sing)
summary(qual)
